tool_description: Get instant access to 140+ million property records, owner details, home value and rent estimates, active listings and rental market statistics with the Realty Mole real estate data API. Available nationwide in the US.
title: Realty Mole Property

api_list.name: Property Rental Listings
api_list.description: Search for rental listings in a geographical area or around a specific location. Returns the listed rent, date, property features, and other listing information. [More info.](https://rapidapi.com/realtymole/api/realty-mole-property-api/details)

parameters.name: state
parameters.description: The two-character state abbreviation, used to search for listings in a specific state

parameters.name: status
parameters.description: The current listing status, used to search for listings matching this criteria. Supported values are: `Active`, `Inactive`

parameters.name: daysOld
parameters.description: The maximum number of days since a property was listed on the market, with a minimum of 1

parameters.name: bedrooms
parameters.description: The number of bedrooms, used to search for listings matching this criteria

parameters.name: propertyType
parameters.description: The type of the property, used to search for listings matching this criteria. Supported values are: `Single Family`, `Condo`, `Townhouse`, `Manufactured`, `Duplex-Triplex`, `Apartment`

parameters.name: latitude
parameters.description: The latitude of the search area. Use the `latitude`/`longitude` and `radius` parameters to search for listings in a specific area

constraints.inter-dependency: latitude, longitude, radius: latitude and longitude must be used together with radius to search for listings in a specific area.

parameters.name: zipCode
parameters.description: The 5-digit zip code, used to search for listings in a specific zip code

parameters.name: bathrooms

parameters.name: address
parameters.description: The address of the property, in the format of 'Street, City, State, Zip'. Used to retrieve data for a specific property, or together with the `radius` parameter to search for listings in a specific area

constraints.inter-dependency: address, radius: address must be used together with radius to search for listings in a specific area.

parameters.name: radius
parameters.description: The radius of the search area, in kilometers. Use in combination with the `latitude`/`longitude` or `address` parameters to search for listings in a specific area

constraints.inter-dependency: latitude, longitude, radius: latitude and longitude must be used together with radius to search for listings in a specific area. address, radius: address must be used together with radius to search for listings in a specific area.

api_list.name: Property Rental Listing by Id
api_list.description: Returns a single property rental listing matching the specified id, if it exists. Property ids can be obtained via the `/properties`, `/saleListings` or `/rentalListings` endpoints. [More info.](https://rapidapi.com/realtymole/api/realty-mole-property-api/details)
api_list.code:
import requests

url = "https://realty-mole-property-api.p.rapidapi.com/rentalListings/{propertyid}"

headers = {
    "X-RapidAPI-Key": "SIGN-UP-FOR-KEY",
    "X-RapidAPI-Host": "realty-mole-property-api.p.rapidapi.com"
}

response = requests.get(url, headers=headers)

print(response.json())

parameters.name: propertyId
parameters.description: The id of the property listing to return

api_list.name: Rental Market Data
api_list.description: Returns rental data for a single US zip code, including rent averages, rental listing composition, and historical rent trends. [More info.](https://rapidapi.com/realtymole/api/realty-mole-property-api/details)
api_list.code:
import requests

url = "https://realty-mole-property-api.p.rapidapi.com/zipCodes/{zipcode}"

headers = {
    "X-RapidAPI-Key": "SIGN-UP-FOR-KEY",
    "X-RapidAPI-Host": "realty-mole-property-api.p.rapidapi.com"
}

response = requests.get(url, headers=headers)

print(response.json())

parameters.description: A valid 5-digit US zip code
